Uncus with basal 1/3 nearly triangular and naked. Valva with costa slightly concave and ventral margin curved, with apex rounded; sella excurved, thumb-shaped, densely bearing thick setae; sacculus with distal 3/5 inflated into a broad and nearly triangular protrusion. Juxta with base wide, distal half bifid into slender, straight, and widely separated arms; anellus with a cluster of short spines (attached to distal end of phallus in Fig. 
24
). Saccus rounded triangular. Phallus long and moderately thick; cornuti presented as a bunch of spines, with a large spine distally and connected with a lanceolate sclerite at base.
